summary:
Energy transition can only be realized through effective and creative combinations of energy saving measures and sustainable energy production, at local and regional level.
Investments will only be sustainable when based on sound feasibility analysis.
Innovative funding and financing approaches.

Effective energy transitions are strongly supported by local sustainable energy organisations: local companies, individuals, homeowners, municipalities need to cooperate to develop their best adapted approaches to reduce energy consumption and implement sustainable energy. Solar panels for individual housing is now economically attractive.

I'm now involved in developing a local energy organisation in Alphen aan den Rijn, Energiek Alphen aan den Rijn (www.energiekalphenaandenrijn.nl). This energy cooperation will be involved in:
- delivery of sustainable energy (electricity, gas) to households and companies;
- developing and realizing sustainable energy projects (solar, wind, biomass);
- establishing cooperation with the municipality, housing corporations and companies;
- develop an energy transition strategy for the region;
- provide information and support to individuals and companies on energy saving measures and sustainable energy;
- cooperate with similar organisations in other municipalities;
- any other activity contributing to sustainable development.

International Projects:
I was team leader for a range of international, Dutch and EU funded, environmental projects:
- Implementation of the EU Chemicals Directives in Turkey (EU-IPA);
- Establishment of Industrial REACH Helpdesks in Turkey (Dutch Agency);
- Development of the National Waste Management Plan for Bulgaria (Dutch Agency);
- Development of an Environmental Master Plan for the Marmara Sea Basin, Turkey (EU-MEDA);
- Development of Environmental Approximation Programmes for Romania and Estonia;
- Implementation of the EU IPPC Directive in Turkey (Dutch Agency);
- UNEP evaluation studies.

profile_positions.description:
Management of international environmental projects in EU accession countries:

Support to the Bulgarian Ministry of Environment to prepare the National Waste Management Program 2008 - 2013, funded by AgentschapNL (Dutch Agency).

Establishment of Industrial REACH Helpdesks in Turkey, funded by AgentschapNL;

Implementation of the EU CHemicals Directives in Turkey, EU-MEDA;

Preparation of an Environmental Master Plan for the Marmara Sea region in Turkey, funbded by EU-MEDA through EIB;

Implementation of the EU IPPC Directive in Turkey, funded by AgentschapNL;

Implementation of the EU Water Framework Directive in Turkey, funded by AgentschapNL;

Implementation of the EU Directive on Portable Batteries in Romania, funded by AgentschapNL

Implementation of the EU Phare 2001 programme in Romania, for the preparation, tendering and monitoring of three EU funded projects: Implementation of IPPC Directive, Implementation of the Water Framework Directive on Pilot Basins, and the Environmental Cost Assessment project, funded by EU Phare.

Several other projects related to environmental approximation in EU accession countries (Poland; Estonia; Hungary; Romania, Bulgaria and Turkey).

Evaluation studies for UNEP:
- Evaluation of the African Sustainable Production and Consumption programme;
- Evaluation of the Environmental Technology Centre in Osaka;
- Evaluation of the UNEP/GEF Climate Change project.

Partner and environmental consultant;
Overall management and financial affairs;
International project development and acquisition
